# Beads (bd) Workflow

Use **bd** for persistent work tracking. Use TodoWrite only for single-session task lists.

## When to use bd vs TodoWrite
- **bd**: Multi-session work, dependencies, discovered follow-up, anything that should outlive the session
- **TodoWrite**: Simple in-session execution checklist (3–5 steps for one session)

## Core commands
- `bd ready` – Find unblocked work
- `bd show <id>` – Issue details and dependencies
- `bd update <id> --status in_progress` – Claim work
- `bd create --title="..." --type=task|bug|feature --priority=2` – New issue (priority 0–4, not "high"/"medium")
- `bd close <id>` – Mark complete; `bd close <id1> <id2>` for multiple
- `bd dep add <issue> <depends-on>` – Add dependency
- **Do not use** `bd edit` – it opens an editor and blocks agents

## Session start
Check `bd ready` for available work. Use `bd show <id>` then `bd update <id> --status in_progress` to claim.

## Session end (Landing the Plane)
Before saying "done":
1. Close completed work: `bd close <id> ...`
2. Create issues for any remaining/follow-up work
3. Sync: `bd sync` (or `bd sync --flush-only` if no git remote)
4. Then complete git workflow: pull/rebase, push; work is not complete until `git push` succeeds.

Run `bd prime` for full, up-to-date workflow context.
